The measurement of hyperfine structures and isotope shifts with high-
resolution laser spectroscopy offers access to the extraction of
fundamental nuclear structure properties including spins, mean-square
charge radii and electromagnetic moments. Within the LISA framework,
a new measurement campaign has been started on Uranium by means of
collinear laser spectroscopy at IGISOL facility. The final aim is the study
